===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In the oracle bone script, it was originally {{zh-l|𠀠}}, a {{liushu|p|nocap=1}} of a [[basket]].

In the bronze inscriptions, {{och-l|丌}} was added under the basket to represent a [[stand]]. It may also have acted as a phonetic component. Hence, the modified version was 𠔝. See also the bottom component of [[眞]].

Later {{Han phonetically borrowed}} for an Old Chinese pronoun. The derivative {{och-l|箕}} refers to the original word.

===Etymology===
; ''third-person possessive pronoun''
: {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} notes its origin is not certain because in the linguistic area pronouns tend to be of the shape KV (K=velar stop; V=vowel). Perhaps Sino-Tibetan; compare {{cog|lus|khi||that}}, {{cog|bo|-ཀྱི, -གྱི|pos=genitive suffix}}, but a Tibeto-Burman /a/ should be expected in this set. Alternatively, {{cog|aav-pro|*ki/ke ~ *ku/ko|pos=third person pronoun}} whose earliest form is perhaps ''*kɨ'' ({{zh-ref|Pinnow, 1965}}) appears to be phonologically closest to the OC word. {{och-l|其|id=2}} may be related to {{och-l|渠|he}}.

; ''modal particle'' "should; probably"
: Probably cognate with {{och-l|期|id=2|stipulated time; time}}, {{och-l|期|id=1|year}} ({{zh-ref|Serruys, 1982}}).

